ion\ncandidates around HIP 8832, HIP 16095 and HIP 95619 are determined as\nbackground contamination. For stars for which we infer the presence of debris\nbelts, a theoretical minimum mass for planets required to clear the debris gaps\ncan be calculated . The dynamical mass limit is at least $0.1 M_J$ and can\nexceed $1 M_J$. Direct imaging data is typically sensitive to planets down to\n$\\sim 3.6 M_J$ at 1 $''$, and $1.7 M_J$ in the best case. These two limits\ntightly constrain the possible planetary systems present around each target.\nThese systems will be probably detectable with the next generation of planet\nimagers.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 18 May 2020 16:24:58 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 5 Jun 2020 14:52:47 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-07-08"}
