quation of state parameter in the\nalternative scenario is given at $1\\sigma$ by $w=0.13\\pm0.17$. Interestingly,\nthe matter bounce and radiation bounce scenarios are compatible with our\nresults. We discuss how these models of oscillatory features can be tested with\nfuture observations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 18 May 2020 18:01:46 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 21 Oct 2020 10:18:54 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-10-22"}
