io distributions of stalled MBHBs in the low-redshift universe, and\nfind that these depend sensitively on binary accretion models. This presents\nthe potential for combined EM and GW observational constraints on merger rates\nand accretion models of MBHB populations.}\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 18 May 2020 18:17:46 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 2 Jun 2020 18:59:14 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-08-19"}
