has two vertices\nand is Ramanujan, and all other examples we computed with $g>1$ and two or more\nvertices were not Ramanujan. In particular, the $(\\ell)^g$-isogeny graph is not\nin general Ramanujan for $g>1$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 18 May 2020 19:03:22 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 15 Oct 2020 18:14:16 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 22 Jan 2021 17:51:11 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Tue, 13 Apr 2021 14:34:36 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Sun, 16 Apr 2023 20:41:49 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-04-18"}
