al spacing suggests that they\nmay be generated by periodic perturbations by the binary, tearing off material\nfrom the inner edge of the outer disk once during each orbit. By comparing\nobservations to hydrodynamical simulations we find that the main features, in\nparticular the gap size, as well as the spiral and streamer filaments, can be\nqualitatively explained by the gravitational interactions of a binary with\nsemi-major axis of $\\sim$35 au on an orbit coplanar with the circumbinary ring.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 18 May 2020 19:14:10 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 4 Jun 2020 18:06:26 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-07-08"}
